        <content type="html" xml:base="https://sacanthias.github.io/projects/eclogue/">&lt;h2 id=&quot;what-it-is&quot;&gt;What It Is&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sheep Protector (working title) is a single-player environmental adventure game, where the player dons the role of a sheepdog attempting to guide a single sheep through a treacherous forest back to the main herd. Along the way, the two encounter obstacles and hostile wildlife, which they must avoid to return home.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h1 id=&quot;development&quot;&gt;Development&lt;&#x2F;h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sheep Protector is still currently in development. We plan to display our game at RIT&#x27;s &lt;a href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;sacanthias.github.io&#x2F;projects&#x2F;eclogue&#x2F;www.rit.edu&#x2F;computing&#x2F;school-interactive-games-and-media&#x2F;ims&quot;&gt;Interactive Media Symposium&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some of the work I&#x27;ve done with Sheep Protector involve the&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;roles&quot;&gt;Roles&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team Lead&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;UI&#x2F;UX Designer&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Programmer&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;tools-used&quot;&gt;Tools Used&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
